      • updatePatternPerformance

        protected void updatePatternPerformance(int performanceType,
                            int patternID,
                            long timePeriod,
                            int frequencyAfterIncrease)
        Update the minimum, maximum, mval, and sval value of a pattern. Remark: frequency is not updated here. frequencyAfterIncrease is required by waiting and sojourn time, because the frequency of the two values may not be the same as the frequency of the manifest
        Parameters:
        performanceType -
        patternID -
        timePeriod -
        frequencyAfterIncrease - if >= 1 then it is used instead of the frequency from patternInfoInt[patternID * 2]
        See Also:
        method

      • getTransStats

        public double[] getTransStats(org.processmining.plugins.petrinet.manifestreplayresult.ManifestEvClassPattern manifest,
                     int encodedTransID)
        Get performance information related to a transition. Since a transition can have more than one pattern, information for each pattern is recorded Aggregated statistics are also calculated and stored in the first IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER elements. For aggregated ones, no standard deviation is measured. The structure of the returned values is [0...(IPerCounter-1) = aggregated stats][IPerfCounter... = info for pattern 1][2*IPerfCounter...] and so on NOTE: frequency of throughput time is the same as waiting and sojourn time. Result: aggregated: [0] = min throughput time; [1] = max throughput time; [2] = average throughput time; [3] = std dev throughput time; [4] = min waiting time; [5] = max waiting time; [6] = average waiting time; [7] = std dev waiting time; [8] = min sojourn time; [9] = max sojourn time; [10] = average sojourn time; [11] = std dev sojourn time; [12] = freq throughput time ; [13] = freq waiting time; [14] = freq sojourn time; for each pattern [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 0] = pattern ID; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 1] = min throughput time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 2] = max throughput time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 3] = average throughput time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 4] = std dev throughput time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 5] = min waiting time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 6] = max waiting time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 7] = average waiting time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 8] = std dev waiting time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 9] = min sojourn time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 10] = max sojourn time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 11] = average sojourn time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 12] = std dev sojourn time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 13] = freq throughput time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 14] = freq waiting time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 15] = freq sojourn time; [IPerfCounter.MULTIPLIER + 16] = freq unique case throughput time;
